In [13]:
def masscut (data, lowBound, upBound):
    index = (data['mass'] > lowBound) & (data['mass'] < upBound)
    values = data[index]
    return values
In [14]:
def yieldvalue (data, values, original):
    ratio = len(values)/len(data)
    newyield = original * ratio
    return newyield
In [15]:
def sig (higgsyield, qcdyield):
    return higgsyield/np.sqrt(qcdyield)
In [16]:
higgscut1 = masscut(higgs_dict, 100, 150)
qcdcut1 = masscut(qcd_dict, 100, 150)
higgsyield = yieldvalue(higgs_dict, higgscut1, 50)
qcdyield = yieldvalue(qcd_dict, qcdcut1, 2000)
print("The higgsYield is :", higgsyield)
print("The QCDYield is :", qcdyield)
print("The expected significance of the mass cut is: ", sig(higgsyield, qcdyield))

In [20]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(14, 2, figsize=(14, 60))
x = 0
for key in higgscut4:
    ax[x,0].set_title("Histogram for " + key)
    ax[x,0].set_xlabel(key)
    ax[x,0].hist(qcd_dict[key], 80, weights=[(2000/2050) * np.ones(len(higgs_mass))],  label='QCD')
    ax[x,0].hist(higgs_dict[key], 80, weights=[(50/2050) * np.ones(len(higgs_mass))],  label='Higgs')  
    ax[x,1].set_title("Histogram for " + key + " with mass cuts")
    ax[x,1].set_xlabel(key)
    ax[x,1].hist(qcdcut4[key], 80, weights=[(2000/2050) * np.ones(len(qcdcut4))],  label='QCD')
    ax[x,1].hist(higgscut4[key], 80, weights=[(50/2000) * np.ones(len(higgscut4))],  label='Higgs')
    x += 1
fig.tight_layout()
plt.show()

From the graph above we can tell that d2, ee2 and mass show high discrimination between the signal and background. We also can see the difference between the histogram and the histogram after the mass cut, this has improved our significance, but only by a small amount.

def d2cut (data, lowBound, upBound):
    index = (data['d2'] > lowBound) & (data['d2'] < upBound)
    values = data[index]
    return values

Part 3: 95% Confidence Level of signal yields¶

In the low luminosity data, the observed significance is less than 5 . We will calculate the 95% confidence level upper limit of signal yield. Evaluate the expected 95% confidence level upper limit

In [55]:
def upperLimit(data,bkgd):
    return data - stats.poisson.ppf((1-0.95)*stats.poisson.cdf(data,bkgd), bkgd)
In [59]:
qcd_low = 2000/(50 + 2000)*len(lowLumi)
upper_limit = upperLimit(len(lowLumi), qcd_low)
print("95 percent confidence level upper limit without event: ", upper_limit)

95 percent confidence level upper limit without event:  48.0
